review_blob: I thought this stout was much better than its been given credit for.  Good coffee aroma, thick, but a little light for a stout. Smooth finish, definitely not the best one out there, but a lot better then the ratings on here.
fruitry aroma, promising a hop taste the flavor doesnt support. little head, disappears quickly, good after taste, lingering hops. all in all a good beer, could use a tad more hops
Wonderful chocolate aroma, followed by a rich malted taste, full chalky mouth feel, a beautiful sustained head. Overall the best chocolate stout Iver ever had

Purchased in a bottle, probably much better on cask. Very strange hop aroma, followed by and even odder hop taste. Very light tasting, as well as colored. Small head, diminished quickly, unusual after taste, almost lemony. Not as good as I had hoped, all in all a strong product.

no smell, no head, no hops, shite.
this beer had a week aroma, followed by a bland hopless flavor, finished off by a stinging over carbonated bite, nothing good to say.
good smell, a bit sweet. taste follows up with a sugary flavor up front, followed by the promised bitter. overall a good beer, could use a tad more hops.
large sustained head, rich sweet aroma, sweet alchoholic taste. a great beer
Full, fluffy head, that lasts.  Sweet alcohol smell, followed by a light but rich taste. Over all not my favorite belgian, but definitely a great beer.
On cask, qutie a good find. good up front hops, doesnt last through the aftertaste, generally a good buy.
very light color, light carbonation a plus.  subtle citrus hop, very drinkable.  not quite as good as id hope, but highly respectable for a golden ale, definitely worth a try
poured with a thin head, disappeared instantly. horribly smell, worst taste. resembles something budweiser would produce. the absolute worst youngs ever had, a bitter disappoinment
Good hoppy aroma, and a decent follow up in the taste.  Carbonation is a little annoying, could use more hops in the flavor. Overall a good beer, didnt see the great aromas everyone else talked of.
relatively odorless, week pour, almost no head.  flavor is a little lacking, decent hope taste, almost no malts, generally a poor offering.

Purchased in a bottle, poured with a small head, that disappeared almost instantly.  Peculiar (living up to its name) sweet flavor, definitely taste the alcohol. A very dark color, almost porterish, hints of red when you hold it up to the light. All in all a surprisingly good buy, likely to try it again
A strange, almost caustic aroma. Pours with almost no head.  Carbonation seems forced, poor bitter taste, almost no hops, all in all a weak offering
Wonderful cascading head, deep malty taste, great earthy aroma. One of my favorite stouts out there.
